==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Howler
<hw>Howl"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
howls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any South American monkey of the
genus <gen>Mycetes</gen>. Many species are known. They are arboreal in
their habits, and are noted for the loud, discordant howling in which
they indulge at night.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Howlet</ent>⟦br⟧
